com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.repeatinggroup

Class RepeatingGroupEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.repeatinggroup.RepeatingGroupEntry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IRepeatingGroupAccessor, IBindable<ListIterator<ITagValue>>, IFIXBytesImportable, ITagValueIterableFromTag<ListIterator<ITagValue>>, ITagValueIteratorBindable<ListIterator<ITagValue>>, ITagValues, ITagValuesReadable, Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<ITagValue>
    Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public final class RepeatingGroupEntry
extends Object
implements IRepeatingGroupAccessor, ITagValues
    An entry in a FIX repeating group. It is itself an ITagValues so that it can contain fields, and a IRepeatingGroupAccessor to support nested repeating groups.

      • addField

        @Deprecated
public void addField(ITagValue field)
        Deprecated. 
        Add the given field to the end of the list of fields.

        Note that ITagValue objects may be reused across multiple method invocations by ITagValues implementations. If you retrieved the 'field' object from a different ITagValues you should make a copy and pass the copy into this method.

        Alternatively, you can use ITagValues.addField(int, IValue) which does exactly that, e.g. addField(field.getTag(), field.getValue()).

        Specified by:
        addField in interface ITagValues

      • getFreeTagValue

        @Deprecated
public ITagValue getFreeTagValue()
        Deprecated. 
        Returns a free tag value object, creating one if necessary.

        This is a better way of getting ITagValue objects than creating them yourself using new. This method allows tag value field reuse in reused messages. The idea is that when ITagValues.clearTagValues() is called on an ITagValues, any ITagValue objects are not discarded, but instead are saved and used as a "free pool", accessible through this method.

        The IValue part of the returned tag value must not be null.

        Specified by:
        getFreeTagValue in interface ITagValues
        Returns:
        ITagValue object

      • removeAllFields

        @Deprecated
public void removeAllFields(BitSet tagsToRemove)
        Deprecated. 
        Removes all instances of the specified fields.

        This method is a more efficient alternative to ITagValues.removeAllFields(int), which must be called repeatedly for each tag.

        Specified by:
        removeAllFields in interface ITagValues
        Parameters:
        tagsToRemove - A BitSet that defines the tags to remove. The bit index corresponds to a specific tag number; setting a bit to true indicates that the tag should be removed if present in the message. It is recommended that the caller does not create a new set for each call, in order to eliminate garbage creation.

      • iterator

        @Deprecated
public ListIterator<ITagValue> iterator()
        Deprecated. 
        Description copied from interface: ITagValueIterableFromTag
        Create an iterator over a collection of ITagValues.

        The following methods are not supported by the returned iterator:

        • java.util.ListIterator#remove()
        • java.util.ListIterator#add()
        • java.util.ListIterator#set()

        Calling any of them results in an UnsupportedOperationException.

        This method guarantees that a new iterator instance is returned with each call.

        The ITagValue objects returned are references to the underlying data, however, there are no guarantees regarding whether objects are created or not. Changing the values of these objects changes the underlying data. To avoid this behaviour you can use ITagValue.copyFrom(ITagValue) to copy the returned value before modifying it. If you intend on storing the returned ITagValue then copying it first is highly recommended.

        Specified by:
        iterator in interface ITagValueIterableFromTag<ListIterator<ITagValue>>
        Specified by:
        iterator in interface Iterable<ITagValue>
        Returns:
        Iterator over ITagValues. Guaranteed to be a new instance for each call.

      • bind

        @Deprecated
public ListIterator<ITagValue> bind(ListIterator<ITagValue> iterator,
                                                ITagValue buffer)
        Deprecated. 
        Description copied from interface: ITagValueIteratorBindable
        Bind an iterator to a collection of ITagValues.

        This method binds the specified iterator to the collection of ITagValues and resets it to the start so that iteration is over the complete collection. If an attempt is made to pass an incompatible iterator type a ClassCastException is thrown. It is possible to check beforehand using the IBindable.isBindable(Object) method.

        The caller may specify the return value buffer. This is like to be very efficient and is guaranteed not to involve object creation. However, modifying the ITagValue entry during iteration has no effect.

        If no return value buffer is specified then modifying the ITagValue entry modifies the underlying data, however, there are no guarantees about object creation.

        Specified by:
        bind in interface ITagValueIteratorBindable<ListIterator<ITagValue>>
        Parameters:
        iterator - The iterator to bind to this collection. May be null, in which case a new iterator is created which is suitable for subsequent reuse.
        buffer - The buffer via which to return ITagValue entries. May be null in which cases the implementation chooses the most efficient return buffer. If supplied then modifying the returned ITagValue entries has no effect.
        Returns:
        Iterator over ITagValues using the supplied buffer to refer to each underlying element. The supplied iterator (provided it was not null) initialized to the start of the collection.

        a repeating group with no entries (ie numInGroup tag = 0)
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given tag is not valid for that particular message type according to the dictionary.
        IllegalStateException - If a group with the given tag already exists or if there's no message type or dictionary name specified.
